CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 21, 1971, pg. 21 reads: "Crowning Queen - Youth and beauty were part of the recent Frog Week festivities when Wrenna Watson (right) last year's "Miss Frog Week," crowned her successor, Sharon Youngue (seated). Looking on is the Frog Week Queen of two years ago, Lisa Bookert.  The girls have several things in common, one being that they are the daughters of Frog Club members.  Wrenna is the daughter of Judge Warren Watson; Sharon's parents are Dr. and Mrs. Eugene Youngue, while Lisa is the daughter of Dr. and Mrs. Charles Bookert. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Two men and woman standing in front of table with four seated women, including Wrenna Watson, second from right, in William Penn Hotel for FROGS week formal
